      "permalink": "https://www.instagram.com/p/DYm4M2XlHbQ/",
      "title": "The most expensive seller mistake I see in Park Cities homes isn't choosing the ",
      "head": {
        "permalink": "https://www.instagram.com/p/DYm4M2XlHbQ/",
        "timestamp": "2026-05-21T17:00:00+0000",
        "media_type": "CAROUSEL_ALBUM",
        "caption": "The most expensive seller mistake I see in Park Cities homes isn\u2019t choosing the wrong agent.\n\nIt\u2019s the renovation that didn\u2019t need to happen.\n\nA $40K kitchen 60 days before listing rarely returns $40K. Buyers see a clean, updated kitchen, not a story about how much was spent. Appraisals look at comps, not your remodel receipts.\n\nMeanwhile, $4K of strategic prep, staging the spaces that matter most in photos, clearing the kitchen \u201cstuff zone,\u201d consistent lighting, paint touch-ups, and refreshed landscaping, often delivers the same final sales price.\n\nThe difference is whether the money shows up in the buyer\u2019s emotional connection to the home or in your closing statement.\n\nIf you\u2019re thinking about renovating before listing in Highland Park, University Park, or Preston Hollow, DM me the address before you start. I\u2019ll tell you what\u2019s worth doing and what isn\u2019t.\n\n#DallasRealEstate #DallasRealtor #HighlandParkTX #UniversityParkTX #ParkCitiesRealEstate #PrestonHollow #DallasLuxuryHomes #MelissaMettryRealEstate #SellerPrep",
